ter with public safety or security director of the intuition of higher education.  In compliance with this Act, any student, faculty or staff member who is required to register as a sex offender must register in person within 3 days of beginning classes or employment at the University of Illinois at Chicago Police Department.  Those that are required to register will complete the below form in person Monday through Friday between 7am-3pm, or by appointment.   Complete the Institutions of Higher Education Employment/Student Information Form  Submit State identification card   943 W. Maxwell St Chicago IL 60638 (312) 99 6-6669  For sex offenders near UIC campus or in Illinois can search the Illinois State Police sex offender database .          Crime Data    Back to main content           Annual Safety Report    Clery Act    Daily Crime Log    Sex Offender Registration                   UIC Logo         University  Police           Locations    Springfield    Urbana-Champaign    Regional Campuses      Related Links    Office of the Vice Chancellor of Administrative Services    Office of Preparedness and Response    Housing    Office of Access and Equity    Campus Advocacy Network    Dean of Students    Transportation Services    Parking         Contact   943 West Maxwell Street, MC 268, Chicago, IL 60608-1563  Phone: Emergency:  (312) 355-5555 | General: (312) 996-2830  uicpd@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  Â© 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 